{
  "stem": "23942.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So there wasn't time enough to-- to establish schools and things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But they tried to teach us, to get us slowly back to what we were, who we were, you understand.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the children, some of them were not reachable because they were with-- non-- every one of these children were either hidden or they were with Polish, you know, with Catholics.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they-- they had to-- they had to take time till they come back, till they realize who you are.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it wasn't-- it wasn't so simple like you think.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, so it's like trying to unite a nation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like you come to Israel from all parts of the world, and you try to make it into one.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this wasn't easy, because each child had a different background during the war, you understand?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You-- you had to-- we had to be molded into slowly to becoming we, you understand?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were different ages, so it wasn't a simple task to send-- anyway, this happened a little later.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I was in Krakow and I was introduced to songs, Jewish songs, and slowly, slowly, I realized that I am becoming me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "OK?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And like I said, it was a gorgeous city, and going even to the Remuh, I didn't know, I didn't appreciate the Remuh shul.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't understand what the Remuh shul, because I never learned who the Remuh was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It wasn't till years, when I went back to Poland they under-- first I--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Even today I meet people, grown people, women that don't know who Remuh is.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- I-- now I know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have his biography.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know all about him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I saw his shul.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, when I went back the second time, I knew the greatness, what I saw, the Remuh shul.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
